
[1]hawse

   HAWSE, n. hawz. [See Halser.] The situation of a ship moored with two
   anchors from the bows, one on the starboard, the other on the larboard
   bow; as, the ship has a clear hawse, or a foul hawse. A foul hawse is
   when the cables cross each other or are twisted together.
